Description: This effort addresses liquid wastes in two major areas: Oil Pollution Abatement (OPA) and Non-
Oily Waste (NOW). Funding will be utilized to assess new commercial off-the-shelf (COTS), modified off-the-
shelf (MOTS), and developmental products and technologies for application to Navy ships and submarines. The
funding will also be utilized to develop and demonstrate detailed system and performance specifications and
design guidance for the acquisition of cost effective shipboard liquid waste management solutions that meet
existing and anticipated environmental requirements within the constraints of shipboard performance, reliability,
and warship-unique requirements. In addition, the effort will seek common solutions across platforms, and where
possible, across the fleet to provide lifecycle cost savings, logistical efficiency, and improved fleet familiarity.

FY 2026 Plans:
Oil Pollution Abatement:
- Develop implementation plan of bilge cleaners to Fleet
- Continue long-term shipboard evaluation of a commercial centrifugal oil/water separator (OWS)
