Title: Commercial Integration Cell                                                                                                         5.000        5.000         0.000
Description: Information sharing is the foundation of how we conduct any activity in space. Space related threats and operational
sharing with the USG, private sector, and Allies and partners is imperative for day-to-day operations. USSF should be compelled
to develop the structure to manage, enforce, correct, and continually improve on threat I&W as it impacts the operational
environment. As USSF's Commercial Augmentation Space Reserve (CASR) program continues to develop formal processes
for threat information sharing as an incentive for commercial participation, the U.S. Space Forces- Space (S4S) Commercial
Integration Cell (CIC) remains a force multiplier and a catalyst for real- time information sharing with the commercial sector across
security classifications. To enhance and build onto the asymmetrical advantage CIC provides, and as the method by which the
US can execute the CASR program, SSC's Commercial Space Office (COMSO) seeks to enable the enhancement of the CIC's
operationally relevant information sharing capability through CASR's contractual framework, offering the USG surge capacity
beyond the currently limited CIC construct. Funds in this Major Thrust will be executed under PE 1206445SF, Project 651126.

FY 2026 Plans:
Complete test and evaluation phase and begin implementation with a set of directed decision briefings and an implementation
plan finalizing the way in which SpOC, S4S, COMSO and fielded forces will operate with respect to operational environment and
threat sharing with Allies, partners, and private sector.

Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.
Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction,
prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond
to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2027 Plans:
N/A
