D. Acquisition Strategy
Fighting SATCOM Integration leverages Other Transaction Authority (OTA) agreement awards through the Space Enterprise Consortium to rapidly develop prototype
capabilities in operationally relevant timelines. Early risk reduction and delivery of first operational prototypes began in FY 2021. Individual prototype efforts are
competitively awarded fixed-price agreements leveraging non-traditional defense contractors. SATCOM EM&C entered into the Software Acquisition Pathway Planning
Phase in 4th Quarter FY 2024 and will seek approval for entry to the Software Acquisition Execution Phase in 2nd Quarter FY 2026. As part of the software acquisition
pathway, USSF is considering leveraging other acquisition options in addition to the current OTAs to incrementally deliver capability enhancements through multiple
vendors, including options to adopt commercially available or open-source solutions instead of developing government unique products. SATCOM EM&C also leverages
an SE&I contractor to facilitate a vendor agnostic and government-owned solution for the back end DevSecOps systems to integrate the various contractors into a

