C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025      FY 2026      FY 2027
Description: Research and development in emerging and maturing technologies and capabilities for modernizing and
transforming US BICES, US BICES-X and the TNE for improved agility, scalability, access, cybersecurity, and data and
information sharing tools and infrastructure.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue to Develop US BICES-X capabilities including further integration of TNE into the MPE, and development and testing of
coalition ISR capabilities. These efforts will enable the modernization and transformation of the US BICES/BICES-X worldwide
enterprise to enable instantiation or interconnection of any partner network to support any operation.
FY 2027 Plans:
International Intelligence Technology and Architectures (IITA) investment in RDT&E ceases support in development to oversee,
manage, and provide the United States (US) component of the multi-national Battlefield Information Collection and Exploitation
Systems (BICES) with a collaborative environment and intelligence sharing enterprise required for processing and disseminating
critical intelligence information between and among US, North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), allied and coalition forces.

Resources in FY27 support classified activities and are provided on a higher network.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Full decrease of investment in RDT&E ceasing support in development to oversee, manage, and provide the United States
(US) component of the multi-national Battlefield Information Collection and Exploitation Systems (BICES) with a collaborative
environment and intelligence sharing enterprise required for processing and disseminating critical intelligence information between
and among US, North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), allied and coalition forces.

