C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                               FY 2025      FY 2026      FY 2027
Title: Personnel Recovery Command & Control (PRC2) - PRMM Development                                                                 3.022        2.626        1.633
Description: PRC2 will use an Agile Development, Security, and Operations (DevSecOps) strategy to test and field tools and
services for planning and managing search and rescue efforts, and disseminate the related information for personnel recovery.

FY 2026 Plans:
PRC2 Personnel Recover Mission Manager (PRMM) development includes the following:
- Modifications to PRMM 3.1 using Agile DevSecOps in two-week increments
- Increase automation to shorten reporting timeline for Isolated Person (IP) events and locator device alerts
- Improve architecture to include code structure, performance, and stability
- Integrate with National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency's (NGA) Map of the World to improve geospatial tracking
- Increase interfaces with Combat Survivor Evader Locator (CSEL) Common Distress Reporting Systems (CDRS)
- Integrate with AOC Modernization initiatives to increase synchronization with Air Tasking Orders
- Improve human-machine interface based on feedback from the personnel recovery community
- Increase secure communications paths to recovery coordinators and recovery team

Operational Systems Development

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
- Establish pathway to zero trust architecture that secures Personally Identifiable Information (PII) and Personal Health Information
(PHI) material
- Integrate Friendly Force Tracking for increased situational awareness
- Integrate Link 16 for forwarding 15-Line Personal Recovery Reports to vehicles
- Develop urgent, mandated Application Program Interface (API) to Maven Target Workbench (Maven)
- Integrate PRMM's critical Device Alert and Mission Manager data with Maven
- Integrate Weather Wind drift and Sea drift tools to build probabilistic landing zones to aid in search and rescue operations
FY 2027 Plans:
- Will continue development of modifications to Personnel Recover Mission Manager (PRMM) 3.1 using Agile DevSecOps in two-
week increments
- Will continue to increase automation to shorten reporting timeline for IP events and locator device alerts
- Will continue to integrate with National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency's (NGA) Map of the World to improve geospatial tracking
- Will continue to increase interfaces with Combat Survivor Evader Locator (CSEL) Common Distress Reporting Systems (CDRS)
- Integrate with AOC Modernization initiatives to increase synchronization with Air Tasking Orders
- Will continue to improve architecture to include code structure, performance, and stability
- Will increase capabilities to include the Mission Execution Tool and the Personnel Recovery (PR) 15-Line Execution Brief
Redesign
- Will review opportunities to utilize commercial cloud service providers for cost/schedule/performance to fit better with other PR
enterprise tools
- Will continue to integrate Personnel Recover Mission Manager's (PRMM's) critical Device Alert and Mission Manager data with
Maven through the application programming interfaces (API)
- Will integrate Personnel Recover Mission Manager's (PRMM's) Data with Joint Personal Edge Compute Device-Tactical Android
(JPECD-TA) through the application programming interfaces (API)
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding decreased from FY 2026 due to funding realignment toward higher priorities.
