       Change Summary Explanation
       Congress directed the increase of FY26 (+15.000M) for Model-Based Systems Engineering of Threat Systems and scenarios. This is in support of the drive
       to continued development, training, and cross discipline growth between defense stakeholders to assist the transition to Model Based Systems Engineering.
       The project will strengthen the talent pipeline needed for increasingly complex defense challenges. This also assist in advanced Modeling & Simulation gaps in
       support of Department of War (DoW) priorities and Joint Warfighting Concept 3.0.

