Color Weather Radar - Acquisition Strategy is to award a 12-month EMD contract via competitive procedures under an OTA. Preliminary Design Review is scheduled for
3Q FY 2026 and Critical Design Review is scheduled for 4Q FY 2026. Following a Rapid prototyping phase, a Low-Rate-Initial Production (LRIP) for 12 assets will be
initiated in conjunction with a follow-on Rapid Production contract. Prototype installs are projected to start 1Q FY 2027, DT/OT immediately after. Production of the 315
CWRs will start 3Q FY 2027.

Center Console Refresh addresses obsolescence issues in the C/KC-135 flight deck and fuel management system through a competitively awarded development
contract followed by a production and install effort. Major Events/Milestones: Contract award Q3 of FY28; Preliminary Design Review Q2 FY 2029; Critical Design
Review Q3 of FY 2029.

High Frequency Modernization (HFM) addresses obsolescence issues for the KC-135 HF Radio by replacing the ARC-190 HF Radio with the ARC-260 HF Radio. Major
events: ESIS completed Q2 of FY 2024; DT 1 completed Q3 of FY2 2024; DT completed Q3 of FY 2025; DT2 Q2 FY26; OT Q4 FY26; Product CCB Q1 of FY 2027; MS-
C Q1 of FY 2027.

COMM2 Crypto & Data acquisition strategy addresses crypto modernization mandates and DoW directives by executing a 23-month Sole Source, Cost Plus Fixed
Fee EMD contract followed by a 15-month production and installation effort. - Integration & Test timeline: 23 Apr 2025 to 23 Mar 2027, PDR/CDR: Q1 of FY 2026,
Development Test & Evaluation: Q1 of FY 2027, Operational Test & Evaluation: Q2 of FY 2027, Black Label Release: Q2 of FY 2027, Milestone C: Q3 FY 2027,
Installations: Q4 of FY 2027 to Q2 of FY 2030, Operations & Sustainment: Q3 of FY 2030.

MAF Connectivity delivers connectivity solutions for C/KC-135 crews increasing their situational awareness and ability to communicate on the battle field. This effort
utilizes a competitively awarded contract to develop connectivity solutions. Major Events/Milestones: ASP approved on 30 Oct 2024; OTA contract awarded 18 Jun 25;
Increment 1 First prototype installation Q2FY26; Increment 1 DT/OT occurs Q2FY26-Q3FY26.

Hybrid SATCOM delivers resilient, multi orbit SATCOM solutions for the KC-135. This program will utilize a competitively awarded to contract to develop prototypes.
Major Events/Milestones: ASP approved on 30 Oct 2024; OTA contract awarded 18 Jun 25; Increment 2 First prototype installation Q1FY27; Increment 2 DT/OT occurs
Q2FY27.

Multi Sensor: Acquisition Strategy includes selection of passive EO/IR sensor, prototype associated hardware/software, evaluate integration. EN task for HW evaluation
SW test interface development, awarded 18 Feb 2025; 15-Month evaluation/integration effort, awarded 21 Apr 2025.

VLF RoRo: The acquisition strategy for VLF RoRo is currently being drafted. The estimated completion date for the acquisitions strategy is 30 Oct 26.

