Title: Development and Test Support                                                                                                       0.561       0.000         12.796
Description: This effort provides comprehensive test and evaluation (T&E) support for a range of activities critical to fielding new
capabilities. It serves as the primary engineering and logistics enabler for demonstrations, operational assessments, formal test
events, and exercises. The scope includes the rapid integration of emerging commercial and government-developed technologies
onto legacy aircraft, requiring agile and innovative approaches to airworthiness and certification. A key function of this program
is to quantify the operational effectiveness and suitability of both temporary "roll-on/roll-off" solutions and permanent platform
modifications through a cycle of developmental testing (DT), operational testing (OT), and thorough assessments of system
performance, safety, and electromagnetic compatibility (EMC). This effort supports Test and Evaluation Master Plans (TEMPs),
Test Information Sheets (TIS), Airworthiness plans, and risk acceptance memorandums to support expedited fielding authorities.


