- SCI completed all development efforts in FY2026. The FY2026 efforts were used to scope and define requirements for
development efforts within the supply enterprise leading to funding new start programs ILS-S and ELMS.
Title: Foundational Logistics Information Technology Enterprise System (FLITES)                                                             7.903      18.116         14.628
Description: FLITES provides comprehensive item cataloging and provisioning functions for the Logistics business systems, and
will replace the Item Management Control System (IMCS) suite of legacy systems. It is the central repository for the item core
business objects, providing standardization of item cataloging processes, structure, attributes, propagation, and standardized
views for all applicable item types. Additionally, FLITES will receive product structure input from an engineering Product Lifecycle
Management (PLM) type system. FLITES contains the item data that is the core underlying information for every logistics
enterprise system.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue business process transformation, compliance, enhancements, and integration with other systems using agile
incremental releases.
- Continue configuration of commercial platform to provide foundational logistics capability.

Operational Systems Development

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                  FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
- Conduct recurring cyber security and system performance testing concurrent with configuration.
- Finalize and deploy Foundational Logistics Information Technology Enterprise System (FLITES) 1.2 with provisioning capabilities
fully replacing unsupportable 50 year old item management system.
- Continue and complete Federal Logistics Information System (FLIS) efforts for data transformation, increased cyber security, and
Defense Logistics Management Standards (DLMS) and Financial Improvement and Audit Readiness (FIAR) compliance.
- Begin development of Item Application Programming Interfaces (APIs).
- Begin development of cataloging inputs and interfaces with DLMS.
- Continue efforts to meet Identity, Credential, and Access Management (ICAM) and FIAR compliance.
- FLITES will replace Item Management Control System (IMCS) capabilities in FY 2026.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Will continue business process transformation, compliance, enhancements, and integration with other systems using agile
incremental releases.
- Will continue configuration of commercial platform to provide foundational logistics capability.
- Will conduct recurring cyber security and system performance testing concurrent with configuration.
- Will continue and complete development of Item APIs.
- Will continue and complete development of cataloging inputs and interfaces with DLMS.
- Will continue and complete efforts to meet ICAM and FIAR compliance.
- Will begin development of the interface with Theater Integrated Combat Munitions System (TICMS).
- Will begin development of the interface with Enterprise Supply Chain Analysis, Planning and Execution (ESCAPE) system.
- Will begin development of capabilities to subsume the D200 E/F/H system suite to manage requirements and supply positions for
weapon system and aircraft spare parts.
