Note
This program, BA 7, PE 0708610F, project 675207, Integrated Logistics System-Supply (ILS-S), is a new start.
This program, BA 7, PE 0708610F, project 675207, Enterprise Logistics Management System (ELMS), is a new start.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
- LOGIT is a portfolio of programs enabling the DAF logistics enterprise including aircraft maintenance, base-level supply operations, and the authoritative source
for all DAF items for aircraft and vehicles. The DAF logistics enterprise is currently comprised of disparate, antiquated, stovepiped systems and processes leaving
logistics operations inefficient, costly, and vulnerable. The goal of this portfolio is to modernize the logistics IT enterprise for a more efficient, cost-effective, integrated,
standardized, and resilient suite of systems. These systems will also incorporate the latest in cybersecurity measures and meet the statutory IT compliance requirements
including Financial Improvement and Audit Readiness (FIAR). The DAF logistics enterprise is comprised of multiple overarching functional areas to include field-level
maintenance, end-to-end supply chain management, and DAF item cataloging and provisioning. The current programs within this PE include: Enhanced Technical
Information Management System (ETIMS), Foundational Logistics Information Technology Enterprise System (FLITES), Supply Capability Initiative (SCI), Integrated
Logistics System-Supply (ILS-S), Enterprise Logistics Management System (ELMS), and Field Maintenance (Field Mx).

 - ETIMS is the system of record for all Technical Orders (TOs) and fully integrates electronic TOs (eTOs) supporting enterprise-wide distribution and viewing along with
 print-on-demand services. This system supports over 178K users across 385 sites worldwide. ETIMS is set to subsume multiple systems and capabilities terminating
 duplicate capabilities and achieving statutory IT requirements and FIAR compliance. The development efforts for ETIMS were completed in FY2025.

 - FLITES provides the capability to manage comprehensive, accurate, reliable item master data (e.g., accurate identification and authorization of owners and users
 of items). FLITES provides item standardization and configuration management from a single authoritative source ensuring foundational logistics processes are
 executed in concert to support the A4 logistics baseline. It enables key integration and transformation capabilities including Item Unique Identification (IUID) association
 to business transactions; streamlined management of part attributes across supply, finance, engineering, technology, transportation, maintenance, and vendor
 communities; and provide translation capabilities between functional and technical business communities and systems.

 - SCI is focused on modernizing the business processes and fundamentally enhancing supply operations and provide total asset visibility across the supply chain.
 These improvements have been identified in the DAF Logistics Capabilities Transformation Plan targeting improvements to manual processes in requisitioning, order
 management, item cataloging, inventory management, asset management, financial management, and supply chain analytics. This supports the DAF achieving total
 asset visibility at the base retail level enabling intelligent, data-driven decision-making based on accurate supply chain information. This initiative will drive base-level

